Continental, Bosch May Profit From Japan Earthquake, FTD Says

-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 
2011-03-28T06:12:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/continental-bosch-may-profit-from-japan-earthquake-ftd-says.html
Continental AG (CON)  and  Robert Bosch
GmbH  may increase sales of airflow sensors after a Hitachi Ltd.
factory in Ibaraki, north of  Tokyo , was closed because of the
earthquake on March 11, the  Financial Times Deutschland  reported
today, without saying where it got the information.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
 nmagnusson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
